-- Morgan Stanley Names Esteban as Head of Spanish Investment Bank
-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 2013-02-19T16:37:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-19/morgan-stanley-names-esteban-as-head-of-spanish-investment-bank.html
Morgan Stanley  named  Andres Esteban 
to lead its investment-banking operations in Spain.  Esteban, a senior managing director of the investment-
banking division, will take over from  Joaquin Arenas , according
to an internal company statement seen by Bloomberg News. The
contents of the memo were confirmed by Hugh Fraser, a London-
based spokesman for Morgan Stanley.  Bank of America Corp. hired Arenas as head of corporate and
investment banking for Spain, it said in a statement sent
yesterday by Silvia Albert, a Madrid-based corporate
communications firm. Arenas is due to start in May, according to
the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Charles Penty in Madrid at 
 cpenty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
